Package controller.appointment

Class AppointmentOutcomeManager

java.lang.Object
controller.appointment.AppointmentOutcomeManager
public class AppointmentOutcomeManager extends Object
The AppointmentOutcomeManager class provides utility methods for managing Appointment Outcomes such as recording and retrieving.

  • Method Details

    • createNewAppointmentOutcome

      public static void createNewAppointmentOutcome(AppointmentOutcome appointmentOutcome)
      Creates a new appointment outcome and adds it to the database. This method takes an `AppointmentOutcome` object, attempts to add it to the `AppointmentOutcomeDatabase`, and handles any exceptions that may arise during the process. If the outcome is successfully added, it remains stored in the database for future reference. If an error occurs during the operation, an error message is displayed.
      Parameters:
      appointmentOutcome - The `AppointmentOutcome` object to be added to the database.

    • updateAppointmentOutcome

      public static void updateAppointmentOutcome(AppointmentOutcome appointmentOutcome, Diagnosis diagnosis, String typeOfService, String diagnosisID, String consultationNotes)
      Updates the details of an existing appointment outcome and adds a diagnosis. This method updates the given `AppointmentOutcome` object by setting the type of service, diagnosis ID, and consultation notes. The status of the appointment outcome is then updated to "COMPLETED". The updated outcome is stored in the `AppointmentOutcomeDatabase`, and the provided diagnosis is added to the `DiagnosisManager`. If any error occurs during the update process, the exception is caught, and an error message is printed to the console.
      Parameters:
      appointmentOutcome - The `AppointmentOutcome` object to be updated.
      diagnosis - The `Diagnosis` object to be added to the system.
      typeOfService - The type of medical service provided during the appointment.
      diagnosisID - The ID of the diagnosis associated with the appointment.
      consultationNotes - Notes regarding the consultation or findings during the appointment.

    • getAllAppointmentOutcome

      public static List<AppointmentOutcome> getAllAppointmentOutcome()
      Retrieves all appointment outcomes from the database. This method fetches and returns a list of all `AppointmentOutcome` objects stored in the `AppointmentOutcomeDatabase`. The list contains the details of all outcomes recorded for appointments.
      Returns:
      A list of all `AppointmentOutcome` objects in the database.

    • getAppointmentOutcomeByAppointmentID

      public static AppointmentOutcome getAppointmentOutcomeByAppointmentID(String appointmentID)
      Retrieves the appointment outcome for a given appointment ID. This method searches through all appointment outcomes in the database to find the outcome associated with the provided appointment ID. If the outcome is found, it is returned; otherwise, the method returns null.
      Parameters:
      appointmentID - The ID of the appointment whose outcome is to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      The `AppointmentOutcome` object associated with the given appointment ID, or null if no such outcome is found.

    • getPatientsAppointmentOutcomeRecords

      public static List<AppointmentOutcome> getPatientsAppointmentOutcomeRecords(String patientID)
      Retrieves all appointment outcome records for a given patient. This method filters and returns a list of all `AppointmentOutcome` objects that are associated with the specified patient ID. It searches through all appointment outcomes and adds those matching the given patient ID to the result list.
      Parameters:
      patientID - The ID of the patient whose appointment outcomes are to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      A list of `AppointmentOutcome` objects associated with the given patient ID, or null if an error occurs during the process.

    • getAppointmentOutcomeRecords

      public static List<AppointmentOutcomeRecord> getAppointmentOutcomeRecords(List<AppointmentOutcome> recordList, String patientID) throws PageBackException
      Retrieves a list of appointment outcome records for a given list of appointment outcomes and patient ID. This method processes a list of `AppointmentOutcome` objects, fetches the corresponding appointment, diagnosis, and prescription details, and compiles this information into a list of `AppointmentOutcomeRecord` objects. Each record contains detailed information about the appointment outcome, including type of service, consultation notes, medication names, and prescription status.
      Parameters:
      recordList - The list of `AppointmentOutcome` objects that represent the outcomes of various appointments.
      patientID - The ID of the patient whose appointment outcomes are being processed.
      Returns:
      A list of `AppointmentOutcomeRecord` objects, each representing the details of an appointment outcome.
      Throws:
      PageBackException - If there is an error in fetching related data or processing any of the outcomes.

    • getAppointmentOutcomeByDoctorID

      public static ArrayList<AppointmentOutcome> getAppointmentOutcomeByDoctorID(String doctorID)
      Retrieves a list of appointment outcomes for a specific doctor. This method filters the list of all appointment outcomes and returns only those that are associated with the given doctor ID. The outcomes returned represent the results of appointments attended by the specified doctor.
      Parameters:
      doctorID - The ID of the doctor whose appointment outcomes are to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      A list of `AppointmentOutcome` objects that belong to the specified doctor.

    • getNumberOfAppointmentOutcomeByPatientID

      public static int getNumberOfAppointmentOutcomeByPatientID(String patientID)
      Retrieves the number of completed appointment outcomes for a specific patient. This method iterates through all appointment outcomes and counts how many are associated with the given patient ID and have a status of "COMPLETED".
      Parameters:
      patientID - The ID of the patient whose completed appointment outcomes are to be counted.
      Returns:
      The number of completed appointment outcomes for the specified patient.
